This paper deals with the synchronization problem for a network of agents, which is a common topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also considers directed switching communication topologies, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The concept of norm synchronization is also discussed, which is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY, followed by cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
